{
  "texts": [
    "• Tools in Dearth: The symphony of data requires tools that harmonize space and time, interfacing seamlessly with other research software.",
    "Yet, gaps exist in tools that can perform this complex dance.",
    "• Fenced Knowledge: Policies and technological tangles lock knowledge within silos, inhibiting the creation of networks among researchers with common objectives, hindering the collective advancement.",
    "• Adapting Policies: The environment of policies and practice often lags behind the dynamic pulse of new knowledge, failing to respond promptly to emerging insights into shifts in disease risk."
  ]
}